President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. The nominations include Walter Barrows for the Railroad Retirement Board, Sim Farar for the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy, and David S. Shapira for the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. The appointments include Denise Moreno Ducheny for the Board of Directors of the Border Environment Cooperation Commission and the North American Development Bank, Kyle Hipsley as the United States Commissioner for the International Boundary Commission, Robert Stanton for the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation, and Jody Williams as Commissioner for the Bear River Commission. President Obama stated that these individuals will bring dedication and serve the American people well.